lines.text: like the wallpaper sticks to the wall
and like the seashore clings to the sea
like you'll never get rid of your shadow
you'll never get rid of me
let all the others
fight-- and fuss
whatever happens
we've got us
closer than pages-- that stick in a book
we're closer than ripples-- that flow in a brook
strolling down the avenue
closer than a miser or the bloodhounds penalizin' me
closer than smog gets to all of l.a.
closer than jonny to confessing he's gay
not a soul can bust this team in two
we stick together like glue
and when it's sleepin' ti-ime
that's when we ri-i-ise
we start to swing
uh, you think you're so jazz, you
our clocks don't chime-- what a surprise
and they ring
a ding-ding-- happy new year
--me-- now to repeat what i said at the start
don't need a large crowbar to break us apart
we're alone but far from blue
before we get finished, we'll make the town ro-oar
we'll hit all the late spots-- and then a few more
we'll start up at stringy's and maybe groucho
life is gonna be a wow-wow-whee
for my-- shadow and me
before we get finished, we'll make the town roar
we'll hit all the late spots-- and then a few more
we'll start up at stringy's and maybe crap joe
life is gonna be a wow-wow-whee
for my-- shadow and me
